malathong, vetsouvanh ning", "sengsouly, khanthaly", "nunez, heddy l.", "louangsouphom, chanthaly", "xanamane, amonelath", "thongdy, kira"], "date": "2022", "dates": ["2022"], "description": ["The collection documents the many cultural facets and multi-generational perspectives of the Lao immigrant community and their New Year Festival at Wat Thammarattanaram, a Buddhist temple and monastery in Broussard (Iberia Parish), Louisiana. This temple serves as a religious and cultural center for Lao people in the area, hosting multiple cultural events throughout the year, with the largest one being the Louisiana Lao New Year (LLNY) celebrated annually on Easter weekend."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-16T06:37:16.329Z", "group": ["catalog-split-14", "catalog", "main-catalog-split-14"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/2023655241", "image_url": [], "index": 2, "language": ["english"], "location": ["saint martin parish", "lafayette parish", "iberia parish", "louisiana", "broussard", "glenmora"], "number": ["2023655241", "2026-06-15t13:44:50.900000"], "original_format": ["manuscript/mixed material", "collection"], "partof": ["american folklife center", "catalog"], "score": 26.967804, "shelf_id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/2023655241", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["glenmora (la.)", "interviews", "lao (tai people)", "color", "digital photographs", "sound recordings", "louisiana", "buddhism and culture", "lao new year", "religious life and customs", "oral histories", "rites and ceremonies", "broussard (lafayette parish and saint martin parish, la.)", "social life and customs", "iberia parish (la.)", "video recordings", "laotian americans"], "timestamp": "2026-06-16T07:09:11.517Z", "title": "Lao Buddhist New Year Festival in Southern Louisiana : Community Collections Grant Project, 2022", "type": ["manuscript"], "url": "//lccn.loc.gov/2023655241"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_002_mv001/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/afc2022010_002_mv001", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2022010.afc2022010_002_mv001/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010.afc2022010_002_mv001/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2022010.afc2022010_002_ms001/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010.afc2022010_002_ms001/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["xanamane, phanat", "hamdani, badar", "xanamane, phouthone"], "date": "2022-10-06", "dates": ["2022-10-06"], "description": ["Phouthone Xanamane discusses the history of Laos Americans and the tribulations it took to not only leave Laos but to start a whole new life in America. Interview is conducted in Laotian."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-02-07T17:22:25.156Z", "group": ["afc2022010", "lao-buddhist-new-year-festival-in-southern-louisiana"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_002_mv001/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2022010/afc2022010_002/afc2022010_002_mv001.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2022010/afc2022010_002/afc2022010_002_ms001.gif#h=150&w=116"], "index": 3, "language": ["english", "lao"], "location": ["glenmora", "louisiana", "united states"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "video/mp4", "application/pdf", "image/jpeg", "application/x-video"], "online_format": ["image", "video", "pdf"], "original_format": ["film, video"], "partof": ["lao buddhist new year festival in southern louisiana", "american folklife center", "community collections grant project"], "score": 16.37035, "shelf_id": "afc2022010_002_mv001", "subject": ["moving image", "interviews", "lao (tai people)", "ethnography", "louisiana", "rites and ceremonies", "social life and customs", "laotian americans"], "timestamp": "2025-02-07T17:23:19.227Z", "title": "Phouthone Xanamane interview conducted by Phanat Xanamane", "type": ["moving image"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_002_mv001/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_009_mv001/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/afc2022010_009_mv001", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2022010.afc2022010_009_mv001/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010.afc2022010_009_mv001/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2022010.afc2022010_009_ms001/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010.afc2022010_009_ms001/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["xanamane, aet", "xanamane, phanat", "hamdani, badar"], "date": "2022-03-31", "dates": ["2022-03-31"], "description": ["Aet Xanamane is a former pageant queen and speaks of her experience as a member of the Nang San Khan. She also talks about immigrating and growing up in the community. She gives an engrossing first-person account of how the American Laos Villages came to be and the work the community undertook to build their temple. This interview is conducted mostly in Lao."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-02-07T17:22:25.156Z", "group": ["afc2022010", "lao-buddhist-new-year-festival-in-southern-louisiana"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_009_mv001/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2022010/afc2022010_009/afc2022010_009_mv001.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2022010/afc2022010_009/afc2022010_009_ms001.gif#h=150&w=116"], "index": 4, "language": ["english", "lao"], "location": ["glenmora", "louisiana", "united states"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "video/mp4", "application/pdf", "image/jpeg", "application/x-video"], "online_format": ["image", "video", "pdf"], "original_format": ["film, video"], "partof": ["lao buddhist new year festival in southern louisiana", "american folklife center", "community collections grant project"], "score": 16.37035, "shelf_id": "afc2022010_009_mv001", "subject": ["moving image", "interviews", "lao (tai people)", "ethnography", "louisiana", "lao new year", "nang san khan", "rites and ceremonies", "social life and customs", "laotian americans"], "timestamp": "2025-02-07T17:23:19.227Z", "title": "Aet Xanamane interview conducted by Phanat Xanamane", "type": ["moving image"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_009_mv001/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_012_mv001/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/afc2022010_012_mv001", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2022010.afc2022010_012_mv001/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010.afc2022010_012_mv001/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2022010.afc2022010_012_ms001/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010.afc2022010_012_ms001/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["xanamane, phanat", "xanamane, amonelath", "hamdani, badar"], "date": "2022-03-31", "dates": ["2022-03-31"], "description": ["Amonleth Xanamane demonstrates how to cook a typical Laotian dish and her family's favorite: Kao piek. While cooking she talks about passing on her traditions to her younger girls and how much of a struggle it can be to keep alive a culture when you experience it second hand."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-02-07T17:22:25.156Z", "group": ["afc2022010", "lao-buddhist-new-year-festival-in-southern-louisiana"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_012_mv001/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2022010/afc2022010_012/afc2022010_012_mv001.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2022010/afc2022010_012/afc2022010_012_ms001.gif#h=150&w=116"], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "location": ["glenmora", "louisiana", "united states"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "video/mp4", "application/pdf", "image/jpeg", "application/x-video"], "online_format": ["image", "video", "pdf"], "original_format": ["film, video"], "partof": ["lao buddhist new year festival in southern louisiana", "american folklife center", "community collections grant project"], "score": 16.37035, "shelf_id": "afc2022010_012_mv001", "subject": ["moving image", "interviews", "lao (tai people)", "ethnography", "cooking, lao", "louisiana", "rites and ceremonies", "social life and customs", "laotian americans"], "timestamp": "2025-02-07T17:23:19.227Z", "title": "Amonelath Xanamane interview conducted by Phanat Xanamane", "type": ["moving image"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_012_mv001/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_013_mv001/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/afc2022010_013_mv001", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2022010.afc2022010_013_mv001/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010.afc2022010_013_mv001/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc2022010.afc2022010_013_ms001/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010.afc2022010_013_ms001/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["xanamane, phanat", "xanamane, samko", "xanamane, kingston", "hamdani, badar"], "date": "2022-03-31", "dates": ["2022-03-31"], "description": ["Samko Xanamane talks briefly about his own experiences of being sent to America as a teenager without knowing any English; especially coming to rural central Louisiana where he was the first encounter many Americans had had with Asian immigrants. He also explains the festival parade, why the floats are so extravagant and how the judging works."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-02-07T17:22:25.156Z", "group": ["afc2022010", "lao-buddhist-new-year-festival-in-southern-louisiana"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_013_mv001/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2022010/afc2022010_013/afc2022010_013_mv001.gif", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/afc/afc2022010/afc2022010_013/afc2022010_013_ms001.gif#h=150&w=116"], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["glenmora", "louisiana", "united states"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "video/mp4", "application/pdf", "image/jpeg", "application/x-video"], "online_format": ["image", "video", "pdf"], "original_format": ["film, video"], "partof": ["lao buddhist new year festival in southern louisiana", "american folklife center", "community collections grant project"], "score": 16.37035, "shelf_id": "afc2022010_013_mv001", "subject": ["moving image", "interviews", "lao (tai people)", "ethnography", "louisiana", "lao new year", "rites and ceremonies", "social life and customs", "laotian americans"], "timestamp": "2025-02-07T17:23:19.227Z", "title": "Samko Xanamane and Kingston Xanamane interview conducted by Phanat Xanamane", "type": ["moving image"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/afc2022010_013_mv001/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/collections/lao-buddhist-new-year-festival-in-southern-louisiana/about-this-collection/", "https://lccn.loc.gov/2023655241", "https://www.loc.gov/item/2023655241", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2023655241", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2023655241/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/collafc.afc2022010"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["thalanh, sith", "pakdi, inseng", "phoumylay, fancy", "andrew w. mellon foundation", "haggood, sami", "phoumylay, palixay", "xanamane, phouthone", "xanamane, samko", "xanamane, kingston", "sengsouly, meng", "phoumylay, khamsone", "ounechith, bouasone", "american folklife center", "xanamane, aet", "luangphone, nithy", "khambounleuang, oubonlath alee", "somchit, amy", "xanamane, phanat", "hamdani, badar", "malathong, vetsouvanh ning", "sengsouly, khanthaly", "nunez, heddy l.", "louangsouphom, chanthaly", "xanamane, amonelath", "thongdy, kira"], "count": 32, "date": "2022", "dates": ["2022"], "description": ["This collection documents the 2022 Louisiana Lao New Year Festival (LLNY) presented April 15-17, 2022, by Wat Thammarattanaram, a Buddhist temple and monastery in Broussard (Iberia Parish), Louisiana. With the support of a 2022 Community Collections Grant (CCG) from the American Folklife Center's Of the People: Widening the Path! initiative, a community-based research team led by project director Phanat Xanamane, videographer Bader Hamdani, historian Dr. Shane Bernard, and assistant director Sami Sion Haggood documented the social, cultural and environmental expressions that have shaped this important cultural celebration over its 30+ year history."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-07-18T05:07:16.825Z", "group": ["collections-portal"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/collections/lao-buddhist-new-year-festival-in-southern-louisiana/about-this-collection/", "image_url": ["https://www.loc.gov/static/collections/lao-buddhist-new-year-festival-in-southern-louisiana/500_500.jpg"], "index": 7, "items": "https://www.loc.gov/collections/lao-buddhist-new-year-festival-in-southern-louisiana/", "language": ["english"], "location": ["saint martin parish", "lafayette parish", "iberia parish", "louisiana", "broussard", "glenmora"], "number": ["2023655241", "2026-06-15t13:44:50.900000"], "original_format": ["collection", "photo, print, drawing", "film, video"], "partof": ["digital collections", "american folklife center", "lao buddhist new year festival in southern louisiana"], "score": 11.157877, "shelf_id": "~/collections/lao-buddhist-new-year-festival-in-southern-louisiana/about-this-collection/", "subject": ["interviews", "color", "digital photographs", "sound recordings", "local history & folklife", "oral histories", "religion & philosophy", "video recordings"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T07:10:10.593Z", "title": "Lao Buddhist New Year Festival in Southern Louisiana", "type": ["collection"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/collections/lao-buddhist-new-year-festival-in-southern-louisiana/about-this-collection/"}], "resource": {"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/lu/batch_lu_ivysaur_ver01/data/sn88064299/00295874867/1921032501/0285.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:lu:batch_lu_ivysaur_ver01:data:sn88064299:00295874867:1921032501:0284/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/lu/batch_lu_ivysaur_ver01/data/sn88064299/00295874867/1921032501/0285.pdf", "segment_count": 4, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn88064299/1921-03-25/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/lu/batch_lu_ivysaur_ver01/data/sn88064299/00295874867/1921032501/0285.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:lu:batch_lu_ivysaur_ver01:data:sn88064299:00295874867:1921032501:0284/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/lu/batch_lu_ivysaur_ver01/data/sn88064299/00295874867/1921032501/0285.pdf", "segment_count": 4, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn88064299/1921-03-25/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/lu/batch_lu_ivysaur_ver01/data/sn88064299/00295874867/1921032501/0285.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn88064299/1921-03-25/ed-1/?sp=2"], "batch": ["lu_ivysaur_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/louisiana/", "2/united states/louisiana/rapides/", "3/united states/louisiana/rapides/glenmora/"], "contributor": ["louisiana state university; baton rouge, la"], "date": "1921-03-25", "dates": ["1921-03-25"], "description": ["MRS HATDOCK SAVED FROM AH OPERATION Followed Advice of Her Druggists Wife and Took Lydia E Pinkhams Vegetable Compound Chicago 111 I was in bed with a female trouble and inflammation and had four doctors but I none of them did me I any good They all I said I would have to have an operation Ia druggists wife I told me to take Lydia IE Pinkhams Vege I table Compound and II took 22 bottles never missing a dose land at theendof that I time I was perfectly _ I nrpll I have never had occasion to take it again as I have been so well I have a six room flat and do all my work My two sisters are taking the Compound upon my rec ommendation and you may publish my letter It is the gospel truth and I will write to any one who wants a personal letterMrs E H Haydock 6824 St Lawrence Avenue Chicago Illinois Because Lydia E rinkham s Vege table Compound saved Mrs Haydock from an operation we cannot claim that all operations may be avoided by lt but many women have escaped oper ations by the timely use of this old"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2020-10-12T13:32:15.678Z", "group": ["ndnp/lu", "louisiana-state-university-baton-rouge-la-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn88064299/1921-03-25/ed-1/?sp=2", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:lu:batch_lu_ivysaur_ver01:data:sn88064299:00295874867:1921032501:0285/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=483&w=328", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:lu:batch_lu_ivysaur_ver01:data:sn88064299:00295874867:1921032501:0285/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=967&w=657", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/lu/batch_lu_ivysaur_ver01/data/sn88064299/00295874867/1921032501/0285.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 2, "language": ["english"], "location": ["glenmora", "united states", "louisiana", "rapides"], "location_city": ["glenmora"], "location_country": ["united states"], "location_county": ["rapides"], "location_state": ["louisiana"], "mime_type": ["image/jp2", "application/pdf", "text/xml", "image/jpeg", "image/jpeg", "application/json", "text/plain"], "number": ["4", "8", "0", "sn88064299", "5", "2", "7", "1", "6", "9", "0000000002"], "number_edition": ["1"], "number_lccn": ["sn88064299"], "number_page": ["0000000002"], "number_reel": ["0", "0", "2", "9", "5", "8", "7", "4", "8", "6", "7"], "online_format": ["image", "pdf", "online text"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Glenmora patriot"], "partof": ["chronicling ame